


# This file contains the master records for the reading & meaning fields
# of the dictionary. For a better overview and to make it easier to obtain
# non-contradictory data for character variants, it is organized by variant
# groups, with the biggest groups coming first and the characters without
# variants (within the selected gamut of slightly shy of 10000 characters)
# come last. This grouping is a mere convenience; should variant groups be
# modified, changes should be manually made to this file.

# A number of variant groups has been marked `@sync`, followed by the characters
# in that group. In synchronized character groups, the first character in the
# argument to `@sync` is the lead character, which means that all fields for
# the other characters inherit the value given for the lead character in the
# respective field, unless an explicit value is given for the variant. Such
# an explicit value can be given literally or symbolically; where no value should
# appear, the field value has been set to `@null`.

# ⒸⒿⓀⓉⒽⓂ

# Since combining diacritics often don't display well and are difficult to copy-and-paste
# correctly, readings with the pinyin vowel ê have been transcribed with numerical tones
# as ê1, ê2, ê3, ê4.


#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 表意文字空格
# removed as it is punctuation
#	@glyphs	&#x3000;
#   @glyphs	　
#   u-cjk-sym/3000	　	gloss:(space used in typesetting)
